						               													<description>DR JEKYLL AND MR HYDE&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Jekyll and Hyde are locked in a never ending struggle for control. It is not only the control of a real monster &amp;ndash; Hyde &amp;ndash; but also the hidden monster &amp;ndash; Jekyll&amp;rsquo;s addiction to his drug. The players work to uncover Hyde&amp;rsquo;s wickedness while also exploring Jekyll&amp;rsquo;s irresistible urge to let Hyde out. It cannot end well.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This is an Engle Matrix Game so players champion one of the characters of Stevenson's original story. Each turn they pick a question from the game board and answer it. This advances the story but no action is automatic! Players pick another player to be their referee. The ref sets the &amp;quot;to happen&amp;quot; roll. Other players may jump in with counter-arguments forcing a dice rolling contest. Bit by bit events add up to a unique story every time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde is a boxed boardgame. It includes a 20x15 inch game map, a rules book and example of play, and action tokens and a die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;TYPE: Beginner Engle Matrix Game&amp;#10;PLAYERS: 2 to 8&amp;#10;AGE: 12 to adult&amp;#10;DURATION: &amp;frac12; hour&amp;#10;COMPLEXITY: Moderate&amp;#10;REPLAYABILITY: High&amp;#10;COST: $20.00&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
